title: Spring Branch teen killed in accidental shooting
content:
A teenager accidentally shot himself inside an apartment late Friday night while playing with a gun.
Around 10:30 p.m., the 19-year-old was a playing with a gun with several other friends, when the gun accidentally went off inside the apartment located near Long Point Road and Oak Tree Drive. The teen died of a gun shot wound to the head.
Police interviewed the witnesses inside the apartment, but no charges are expected. No other information was available about the teen.
